    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess i get the \"shared state\" thing, but it still feels a bit like magic or something. if there's no signal and no hidden mechanism, it just seems like there's some weird, invisible force or something messing with the particles to make them stay in sync. how do physicists actually reconcile that without it sounding like something out of a fantasy book?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
