      "content": "Physicists reconcile this not as an \"invisible force,\" but as a fundamental property of quantum reality itself, which defies our everyday intuition. The mathematics of quantum mechanics accurately predicts this instantaneous correlation without invoking any hidden variables or classical forces. This randomness and non-locality are intrinsic to how nature behaves at the smallest scales, forcing us to abandon classical assumptions about local reality.",
      "source": "target",
